or the engineer on the outside envelope of each bid and all letters and other transmittals amending or modifying the
bids. Any bid received at the designated location after the time specified must be returned to the bidder unopened.


(f) 

Bid opening. 

The contracting committee will conduct the bid opening in private. The contracting committee will open each bona
fide bid which has been received prior to the deadline, and review it for any irregularities, errors, or exceptions.
It must be verified that any addendum to the specification has been acknowledged by each bidder. The adequacy of bid
bonds or certified checks must also be verified. 

(g) 

Conditions affecting acceptability of bids. 

The borrower must take the following specified action if any of the following exist: 

(1) 

Fewer than three bona fide bids received. 

If fewer than three bona fide bids are received for the contract project, the borrower must obtain REA concurrence
prior to awarding the contract. The borrower may, however, elect to return all bids unopened, make changes in the specification
or the qualified bidders list or both and invite new bids. 

(2) 

